title: American Paintings Boxed Note Cards
description:
Notecards developed from Edward Hopper’s Nighthawks, 1942; Grant Wood’s American Gothic, 1930;  Peter Blume’s The Rock, 1944-48; Mary Cassatt’s The Child’s Bath, 1893; John Singer Sargent’s The Fountain, Villa Torolonia, Frascati, Italy, 1907 from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

A selection of American paintings from the 19th to 20th century from the Arts of the Americas collection.

The cards are made from a sustainable FSC certified mix paper and vegetable-based inks.

  • Card dimensions: 5 x 7 in.
  • Box dimensions: 5.625 x 7.625 x 1.375 in.
  • 20 cards and envelopes, 5 cards each of 4 images.
